+{"id":"frankentorch-rjn4","title":"tensor_diff drops batch dims when last_dim < 2 and silently accepts rank-0 input","description":"FrankenTorchSession::tensor_diff returns shape [0] whenever the input last dim is < 2. PyTorch parity: a [3,1] input must produce [3,0] (leading dims preserved, last dim reduced to 0), not [0]. Same bug duplicated in the F32 branch. Fix: when last_dim<2 return zero-numel tensor with shape[..len-1] ++ [0]; reject rank-0 with explicit error.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:50:32.385666969Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:53:46.900530237Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T20:53:46.898648454Z","close_reason":"tensor_diff now preserves leading dims when the last dim collapses to <2 (e.g. [3,1] -> [3,0] instead of [0]) and explicitly rejects rank-0 input (matches PyTorch's RuntimeError). Both F64 and F32 branches updated; 4 new tests cover the leading-dim preservation and rank-0 rejection paths in both dtypes. All 1086 ft-api tests pass; clippy + ubs clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
